- "gems" refers to products in the marketplace;
- "highly valued" refers to products with a price greater than $10;
- "earned the trust of many" refers to products with a rating greater than 4;
- "names" refers to the titles of the products;
- "artisans" refers to the brands that manufacture the products;
- "worth" refers to the prices of the products;
- "praise" refers to the ratings of the products.

- " Revenue-generating flowers" refers to the top 10 products by total revenue;
- "Most diverse bloomers" refers to the top 5 brands with the highest number of products;
- "Most valuable gardens" refers to the top 3 categories by total value of products;
- "Most prolific gardeners" refers to the top 2 suppliers with the highest number of products.

- 'Shipped' refers to the status of the order being successfully dispatched;
- 'brand_id = 0' refers to a specific brand in the database;
- 'May 2023' is the time period from May 1, 2023, to May 31, 2023.

- "Gems" refers to products;
- "Shining brightly in the inventory" indicates that the products have a positive inventory (`inventory > 0`);
- "Gathered at least 5 reviews" means the products have a `review_count >= 5`.

- "shining stars" refers to products that are featured;
- "garden of commerce" is a metaphor for the product database;
- "nurturing brands and suppliers" refers to the brands and suppliers that provide the products;
- "value of the harvest" refers to the product price.

- "Branches" refers to product categories;
- "Shining stars" refers to top-rated products;
- "Swift delivery" refers to a lead time of less than 10 days;
- "Thriving ecosystem of at least six species" refers to categories with more than 5 products.

- "product" refers to an item listed in the products table;
- "brand" refers to the manufacturer of the product;
- "supplier" refers to the entity that provides the product to the market;
- "combined revenue" is the sum of the revenue generated by a product, its brand, and its supplier.

- "shining star" refers to the brand that is the top performer;
- "leading in total revenue" means the brand with the highest total revenue;
- "customer satisfaction" is measured by the average rating of the products.

- 'In-stock products' refers to products with inventory > 0;
- 'Cost more than the average' refers to products with a price higher than the average price of all products;
- 'Average order total over $50' means the average total cost of orders for the product must be greater than 50.00.

- "Featured products" are those with the `is_featured` flag set to 1;
- "Top 5 brands" are ranked by their average rating in descending order;
- "Category 1" refers to a specific product category.

- Featured products are those marked as important or highlighted by the company;
- Top-rated products have a rating greater than 4.5 and more than 100 reviews;
- Top-selling products are those that generate the most revenue;
- The best product within a brand is the one that ranks first by product ID within its brand category.

- "Blossoms from the same tree but in different sections" refers to products from the same brand but in different categories;
- "Admiration score" refers to the average rating of the product;
- "Names and the name of the tree they grow from" refers to the product title and brand name.

- Total revenue is calculated by summing the total cost of all orders for each product;
- The product with the highest total revenue is the one that appears first when the results are ordered by total revenue in descending order;
- The query uses a Common Table Expression (CTE) to organize and calculate data in a structured manner.

- 'Shipped' status indicates that the order has been dispatched to the customer;
- 'Paid' status indicates that the payment for the order has been received;
- 'Total sales' refers to the sum of the total costs of orders in each category.

- "golden fruits of sales" refers to high total sales;
- "shining stars of customer ratings" refers to high average ratings;
- "average harvests" refers to the average sales and ratings.
